  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it’s tender with a slight bite, then once done, drain and return to the pot and keep covered, then rinse and add the <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> to the brown rice – this is your <strong>edamame brown rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1619774998006-x200.jpg",
